d fileâ€ surprise).</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">â€œUnsplit everythingâ€ (keep only this view)</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">(no need)</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">Ctrl-w o</code></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Closes all other windows, keeps the current one.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h3 class=\"\" id=\"windows--splits-the-viewport-stuff\">Windows / splits (the viewport stuff)</h3>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table class=\"md-table\"><thead class=\"\"><tr class=\"\"><th class=\"md-th\">Move</th><th class=\"md-th\">Keys</th><th class=\"md-th\">Why youâ€™ll use it constantly</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"\"><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">SplitÂ <strong class=\"\">below</strong></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">â  -</code></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Quick â€œstack two viewsâ€ moment. (<a href=\"https://lazyvim.github.io/keymaps\" title=\"âŒ¨ï¸ Keymaps | LazyVim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link group inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400\">LazyVim</a>)</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">SplitÂ <strong class=\"\">right</strong></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">â  |</code></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Your vertical split move. (<a href=\"https://lazyvim.github.io/keymaps\" title=\"âŒ¨ï¸ Keymaps | LazyVim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link group inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400\">LazyVim</a>)</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Close the current split</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">â  w d</code></td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Kill theÂ <em class=\"\">window</em>, keep buffers alive. (<a href=\"https://lazyvim.github.io/keymaps\" title=\"âŒ¨ï¸ Keymaps | LazyVim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link group inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400\">LazyVim</a>)</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">â€œZoomâ€ current split (maximize / restore)</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">â  w m</code>Â (alsoÂ <code class=\"md-inline-code\">â  u Z</code>)</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">tmux-zoom vibe for focus, then pop back. (<a href=\"https://lazyvim.github.io/keymaps\" title=\"âŒ¨ï¸ Keymaps | LazyVim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link group inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400\">LazyVim</a>)</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Resize split</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\"><code class=\"md-inline-code\">Ctrl</code>Â + arrow keys</td><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-4 py-2\">Fast â€œgive this pane more spaceâ€ without thinking. (<a href=\"https://lazyvim.github.io/keymaps\" title=\"âŒ¨ï¸ Keymaps | LazyVim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"external-link group inline-flex items-center text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400\">LazyVim</a>)</td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700 px-